headline: Better Artificial Intelligence (AI) Stock: Nvidia vs. Intel
summary: Both Nvidia and Intel should benefit immensely.  When it comes to investing in artificial intelligence (AI), buying shares of graphics processing unit (GPU) manufacturers like Nvidia (NASDAQ: NVDA) and Intel (NASDAQ: INTC) can be a wise decision.  Nearly every AI application requires these specialized chips to function, and buying stock in a GPU maker gives your portfolio direct exposure to the entire AI industry.

headline: Intel (NasdaqGS:INTC) Sees Leadership Shift As CCO Christoph Schell Departs For CEO Role
summary: Intel (NasdaqGS:INTC) has experienced a 3% price rise over the last quarter, aligning with the broader market uptick where the Nasdaq Composite gained 2%. This movement occurs amid notable executive changes, including the resignation of Chief Commercial Officer Christoph Schell, as well as the appointment of a new CEO, Lip-Bu Tan. The company's earnings report reflected some challenges, posting a net loss, but remained in sync with overall market performances buoyed by optimism from strong...

headline: 1 Stock Under $50 for Long-Term Investors and 2 to Approach with Caution
summary: Stocks in the $10-50 range offer a sweet spot between affordability and stability as they’re typically more established than penny stocks. But their headline prices don’t guarantee quality, and investors should exercise caution as some have shaky business models.
